    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, we have a situation. Security just flagged that 50 user emails were exposed because of a misconfigured S3 bucket for the last few days. It's small, but if the press gets hold of the word 'misconfiguration' or 'leak,' our trust metrics are going to tank. \n\nHow should we frame this to the press? Is there a way to talk about this without making it sound like a security failure?",
