      "content": "The \"routine audit\" angle is okay, but if a tech journalist specifically asks what caused the exposure, saying \"misconfiguration\" still sounds like we messed up the basics. Is there a way we could frame the actual cause of the discrepancy in a way that sounds like it was part of a planned system update or something more technical and intentional?",
