      "content": "\"infrastructure migration\" is better. But honestly, even that sounds like we're covering up a mistake. \n\nWhat if we just didn't call it a \"misconfiguration\" or a \"migration error\" at all? Could we frame it as a temporary data synchronization event or a metadata adjustment phase that just happened to be visible to some users for a bit? I want something that implies this was just a natural part of the system's evolution rather than a mistake we're trying to hide.",
